<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-05T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="418" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1044: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-05T17:00:00-07:00">January 5, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:55 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. The decree calling elections for President to take place on February
                            6th, 7th and 8th was issued on January 3rd.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>